\begin_layout Section
Constant Surface Speed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
CSS or Constant Surface Speed (G96) uses the machine X origin modified by
 the tool X offset to compute the spindle speed in RPM.
 CSS will track changes in tool offsets.
 The X machine origin should be when the reference tool ( the one with zero
 offset) is at the center of rotation.
\end_layout

